&gt;&gt; A person that you
should remember.

00:00:53.270 --> 00:00:56.620
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick: A person
that you should remember.

00:00:56.620 --> 00:00:57.920
Thank you.

00:00:57.920 --> 00:01:00.220
And you?

00:01:03.350 --> 00:01:04.380
&gt;&gt; It's somebody that
spends [inaudible].

00:01:04.380 --> 00:01:05.680
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick:
Okay, that's right.

00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:07.720
That's another definition
for a veteran [inaudible].

00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:09.020
And then you.

00:01:09.020 --> 00:01:10.460
&gt;&gt; Somebody in the Army.

00:01:10.460 --> 00:01:13.940
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick:
Somebody in the Army, yes.

00:01:15.010 --> 00:01:16.310
[ Inaudible Comment ]

00:01:16.310 --> 00:01:21.240
There's a whole collection of what
you just said that's kind of right.

00:01:21.240 --> 00:01:24.750
A veteran in terms of what we're
talking about today, though,

00:01:24.750 --> 00:01:28.890
is somebody that has served in the
military, in any of the military:

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:33.040
Army, Navy, Air Force,
Marine Corps, Coast Guard.

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:37.280
All those people who served in
the military are called veterans,

00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:39.660
once they come out of the service.

00:01:39.660 --> 00:01:41.240
Who in here knows a veteran?

00:01:41.240 --> 00:01:43.950
Who do you know?

00:01:43.950 --> 00:01:45.250
&gt;&gt; Me.

00:01:45.250 --> 00:01:46.550 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick: You're a veteran?

00:01:46.550 --> 00:01:47.850
&gt;&gt; No, [inaudible comment].

00:01:47.850 --> 00:01:49.150
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick: I did.

00:01:49.150 --> 00:01:50.450
Your father?

00:01:50.450 --> 00:01:51.750
What service was he in?

00:01:51.750 --> 00:01:53.050
&gt;&gt; He was in the military.

00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:54.350
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick: Do you
know what service he was in:

00:01:54.350 --> 00:01:55.650
Army, Navy, Marine Corps?

00:01:55.650 --> 00:01:56.950
&gt;&gt; Marines.

00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:58.250
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick: He's Marines?

00:01:58.250 --> 00:01:59.550
That's why you got a
good haircut, right?

00:01:59.550 --> 00:02:00.850
Okay, yes, you.

00:02:00.850 --> 00:02:02.150
&gt;&gt; My grandfather.

00:02:02.150 --> 00:02:03.450
&gt;&gt; Robert Patrick:
Your grandfather was.

00:02:03.450 --> 00:02:04.750
Do you know what service he was in?

00:02:04.750 --> 00:02:06.660
Marines? My gosh, we got
a bunch of marines here.

