00:36:00.730 --> 00:36:04.150
to be drafted whether
you liked it or not.

00:36:04.150 --> 00:36:08.350
Most people don't like that at all.

00:36:11.190 --> 00:36:13.420
I was in college.

00:36:13.420 --> 00:36:15.610
I was flunking out of college.

00:36:15.610 --> 00:36:17.150
In fact, I did.

00:36:17.150 --> 00:36:21.390
Fifty years ago, I had
flunked out of college.

00:36:22.860 --> 00:36:28.400
And when I went back to
school, ROTC was available.

00:36:28.400 --> 00:36:33.890
If you were in ROTC, you
were deferred from the draft.

00:36:33.890 --> 00:36:36.870
But you went in as a
commissioned officer.

00:36:36.870 --> 00:36:40.750
And an officer is responsible
for everything

00:36:40.750 --> 00:36:43.920
that his unit does and doesn't do.

00:36:43.920 --> 00:36:46.940
I wanted to find out
if I could do that.

00:36:46.940 --> 00:36:52.020
I wanted to find out if I
could get men to do something

00:36:52.020 --> 00:36:55.860
that they didn't want to do
in a hostile environment.

00:36:55.860 --> 00:36:58.400
I didn't know if I'd like it.

00:36:58.400 --> 00:37:02.420
Didn't know if I would
thrive on that.

00:37:02.420 --> 00:37:05.140 position:56%
But wanted to know if I could do it.

00:37:05.140 --> 00:37:10.040
And those were my reasons
for going ROTC.

00:37:10.040 --> 00:37:12.340
Yes ma'am.

00:37:18.230 --> 00:37:23.440
No. You need the practice of
speaking into the microphone.

00:37:23.440 --> 00:37:25.410
I'm sorry.

